---
// Last Light — GitHub maintenance agent
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8" />
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
	<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/logo.png" />
	<title>Last Light — GitHub Maintenance Agent</title>
	<meta name="description" content="An open-source agent that keeps the lights on in your GitHub repos. Triages issues, reviews PRs, monitors repo health — so you can focus elsewhere." />
	<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
	<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
	<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;600&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

	<!-- Hero -->
	<header class="hero">
		<div class="hero-content">
			<img src="/logo.png" alt="Last Light logo" class="hero-logo" />
			<p class="hero-name">Last Light</p>
			<h1>Keep the lights on <span class="accent">after you've moved on</span></h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				An open-source agent that looks after repos in maintenance mode.
				Triages issues, reviews PRs, chases down stale items — so you can focus on what's next.
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a href="#get-started" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
				<a href="https://github.com/cliftonc/lastlight" class="btn btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View Source</a>
				<a href="https://github.com/users/cliftonc/projects/4" class="btn btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Roadmap</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</header>

	<!-- What it does -->
	<section class="features" id="features">
		<h2>Keeping the lights on</h2>
		<div class="feature-grid">
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon">
					<svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h3>Issue Triage</h3>
				<p>Labels, deduplicates, and chases missing info. Real-time with webhooks, or every 15 minutes via cron.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon">
					<svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="7" r="4"/><polyline points="17 11 19 13 23 9"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h3>PR Review</h3>
				<p>Reads the diff, leaves honest feedback. Instant via webhooks, or polled every 30 minutes. Critical issues first, nits last.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon">
					<svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h3>Health Reports</h3>
				<p>Monday morning summary of what's piling up, what's gone stale, and what needs you.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon">
					<svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M19.4 15a1.65 1.65 0 00.33 1.82l.06.06a2 2 0 010 2.83 2 2 0 01-2.83 0l-.06-.06a1.65 1.65 0 00-1.82-.33 1.65 1.65 0 00-1 1.51V21a2 2 0 01-4 0v-.09A1.65 1.65 0 009 19.4a1.65 1.65 0 00-1.82.33l-.06.06a2 2 0 01-2.83 0 2 2 0 010-2.83l.06-.06A1.65 1.65 0 004.68 15a1.65 1.65 0 00-1.51-1H3a2 2 0 010-4h.09A1.65 1.65 0 004.6 9a1.65 1.65 0 00-.33-1.82l-.06-.06a2 2 0 012.83-2.83l.06.06a1.65 1.65 0 001.82.33H9a1.65 1.65 0 001-1.51V3a2 2 0 114 0v.09a1.65 1.65 0 001 1.51 1.65 1.65 0 001.82-.33l.06-.06a2 2 0 012.83 2.83l-.06.06A1.65 1.65 0 0019.4 9a1.65 1.65 0 001.51 1H21a2 2 0 010 4h-.09a1.65 1.65 0 00-1.51 1z"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h3>Two modes</h3>
				<p>Webhooks for real-time response, or cron for periodic sweeps. Use one or the other — not both.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- How it works -->
	<section class="how-it-works">
		<h2>How it works</h2>
		<p class="section-desc">
			Built on <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hermes Agent</a>
			with a custom MCP server packing 28 GitHub tools.
			Authenticates as its own GitHub App — every action is clearly from the bot, not you.
		</p>
		<div class="architecture">
			<div class="arch-step">
				<span class="step-num">1</span>
				<div>
					<strong>Point it at your repos</strong>
					<p>List what you want watched in <code>.hermes.md</code></p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="arch-step">
				<span class="step-num">2</span>
				<div>
					<strong>You move on to other things</strong>
					<p>Cron jobs keep running — scanning for new issues, unreviewed PRs, stale items</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="arch-step">
				<span class="step-num">3</span>
				<div>
					<strong>Last Light gets to work</strong>
					<p>Labels, reviews, closes duplicates, writes reports</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="arch-step">
				<span class="step-num">4</span>
				<div>
					<strong>The repo stays healthy</strong>
					<p>Everything happens on GitHub — comments, labels, reviews. No extra dashboard to check</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p class="section-note">Already have an <code>AGENTS.md</code> or <code>CLAUDE.md</code> in your repo? Last Light reads those automatically — your coding conventions, testing requirements, and architectural guardrails carry over. No need to duplicate them.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Get started -->
	<section class="get-started" id="get-started">
		<h2>Light it up</h2>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 1</span> Install Hermes Agent</h3>
			<pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/main/scripts/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 2</span> Clone Last Light</h3>
			<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/cliftonc/lastlight.git
cd lastlight</code></pre>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 3</span> Create a GitHub App</h3>
			<p>
				Head to <a href="https://github.com/settings/apps/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/settings/apps/new</a> and create an app with these permissions:
			</p>
			<ul class="permissions-list">
				<li><strong>Issues</strong> — Read & Write</li>
				<li><strong>Pull Requests</strong> — Read & Write</li>
				<li><strong>Contents</strong> — Read & Write</li>
				<li><strong>Metadata</strong> — Read</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Generate a private key, save the <code>.pem</code> file into the lastlight folder, and install the app on your repos.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 4</span> Configure</h3>
			<pre><code>cp .env.example .env
cp config.yaml.example config.yaml</code></pre>
			<p>Fill in your GitHub App credentials in <code>.env</code>:</p>
			<pre><code>GITHUB_APP_ID=123456
GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=./your-app.private-key.pem
GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID=789012</code></pre>
			<p>Then add your repos to <code>.hermes.md</code>:</p>
			<pre><code>## Managed Repositories
- yourname/your-repo
- yourname/another-repo</code></pre>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 5</span> Choose a model</h3>
			<p>Last Light needs an LLM to think with. Set the provider and model in <code>config.yaml</code>:</p>
			<pre><code>model:
  default: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4  # or any model your provider supports
  provider: openrouter                # routes to 100+ models via one key</code></pre>
			<p>Then add your API key to <code>.env</code>. Pick whichever provider you prefer:</p>

			<div class="backends-grid">
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://openrouter.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a></h4>
					<p>One API key, many models. OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, open-source — all through one endpoint.</p>
					<pre><code>OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4>OpenAI</h4>
					<p>Direct access to GPT and Codex models.</p>
					<pre><code>provider: openai
# or: provider: openai-codex</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4>Anthropic</h4>
					<p>Direct access to Claude models.</p>
					<pre><code>provider: anthropic</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4>AWS Bedrock</h4>
					<p>Use models via your AWS account. Needs AWS credentials configured.</p>
					<pre><code>provider: bedrock</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hugging Face</a></h4>
					<p>Open models via inference providers. Free tier included.</p>
					<pre><code>HF_TOKEN=hf_...</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://opencode.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenCode</a></h4>
					<p>Curated models (GPT, Claude, Gemini, open-source). Pay-as-you-go.</p>
					<pre><code>OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=...</code></pre>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 6</span> Pick a terminal backend</h3>
			<p>Last Light runs commands through Hermes Agent's terminal. By default it uses <code>local</code> — commands run directly on your machine. For isolation or remote execution, pick a different backend in <code>config.yaml</code>. See the <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/user-guide/configuration" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hermes configuration docs</a> for full details:</p>

			<div class="backends-grid">
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4>Docker</h4>
					<p>Sandboxed container with dropped capabilities, PID limits, and tmpfs. Needs Docker installed.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: docker</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://modal.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Modal</a></h4>
					<p>Cloud VM sandbox. Ephemeral, scalable, great for evals. Needs a Modal account.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: modal</code></pre>
					<p>Set <code>MODAL_TOKEN_ID</code> and <code>MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET</code> in <code>.env</code>.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4>SSH</h4>
					<p>Run on a remote server. Persistent shell with connection reuse. Good for beefy hardware.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: ssh</code></pre>
					<p>Set <code>TERMINAL_SSH_HOST</code> and <code>TERMINAL_SSH_USER</code> in <code>.env</code>.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://www.daytona.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Daytona</a></h4>
					<p>Managed cloud dev environment with stop/resume. Needs a Daytona API key.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: daytona</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card">
					<h4><a href="https://apptainer.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Singularity</a></h4>
					<p>For HPC clusters and shared machines where Docker isn't available. Uses Apptainer/Singularity.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: singularity</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="backend-card backend-not-recommended">
					<h4>Local <span class="badge-warn">not recommended</span></h4>
					<p>Commands run directly on your machine. No isolation — the agent has full access to your filesystem.</p>
					<pre><code>terminal:
  backend: local</code></pre>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p>All container backends support resource limits:</p>
			<pre><code>terminal:
  container_cpu: 1         # CPU cores
  container_memory: 5120   # Memory in MB
  container_disk: 51200    # Disk in MB
  container_persistent: true</code></pre>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 7</span> Connect a gateway <span class="step-label">optional</span></h3>
			<p>Talk to Last Light from Discord, Slack, Telegram, and more. See the <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/user-guide/messaging" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hermes gateway docs</a> for the full list. Run the setup wizard:</p>
			<pre><code>./lastlight gateway setup</code></pre>
			<p>Then run it as a persistent service:</p>
			<pre><code>./lastlight gateway            # run in foreground
./lastlight gateway install    # install as a system service</code></pre>

			<div class="gateway-grid">
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4>Discord</h4>
					<p>Create a bot at the <a href="https://discord.com/developers/applications" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord Developer Portal</a>. Enable <strong>Presence Intent</strong> and <strong>Message Content Intent</strong> under Privileged Gateway Intents or the bot won't connect.</p>
					<pre><code>DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your-token
DISCORD_HOME_CHANNEL=channel-id</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4>Slack</h4>
					<p>Create an app at <a href="https://api.slack.com/apps" target="_blank" rel="noopener">api.slack.com/apps</a> with bot token scopes, then set in <code>.env</code>:</p>
					<pre><code>SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...</code></pre>
				</div>
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4>Telegram</h4>
					<p>Create a bot via <a href="https://t.me/BotFather" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@BotFather</a>, then set in <code>.env</code>:</p>
					<pre><code>TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-token
TELEGRAM_HOME_CHANNEL=chat-id</code></pre>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 8</span> Set up GitHub webhooks <span class="step-label">optional</span></h3>
			<p>Make Last Light react to repo events in real time — new issues, PRs, comments. This uses a single webhook endpoint that your GitHub App sends all events to. The agent decides what to act on based on the prompt you configure.</p>

			<h4>1. Enable the webhook platform</h4>
			<p>Add to <code>config.yaml</code>:</p>
			<pre><code>platforms:
  webhook:
    enabled: true
    extra:
      host: "0.0.0.0"
      port: 8644
      routes:
        github:
          secret: "your-webhook-secret"
          events: ["issues", "pull_request", "issue_comment"]
          skills: ["webhook-github"]
          prompt: |
            GitHub event: &#123;_event_type&#125;, action: &#123;action&#125;
            Repository: &#123;repository.full_name&#125;
            Issue/PR: #&#123;issue.number&#125; &#123;issue.title&#125;
            Author: &#123;issue.user.login&#125;
            Body: &#123;issue.body&#125;
          deliver: log</code></pre>
			<p>The <code>prompt</code> passes event data to the agent. The actual logic — what to act on, what to ignore — lives in the <code>webhook-github</code> skill at <code>skills/webhook-github/SKILL.md</code>, which is easy to customise.</p>

			<h4>2. Configure your GitHub App</h4>
			<p>In your GitHub App settings, enable the webhook and set:</p>
			<ul class="permissions-list">
				<li><strong>Webhook URL</strong> — <code>http://your-host:8644/webhooks/github</code></li>
				<li><strong>Secret</strong> — same secret as in <code>config.yaml</code></li>
			</ul>
			<p>The endpoint must be publicly reachable. Use <a href="https://ngrok.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ngrok</a> or <a href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/connections/connect-networks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Tunnel</a> if running locally.</p>

			<h4>3. Choose what happens</h4>
			<p>The <code>deliver</code> option controls where the agent's response goes:</p>
			<div class="gateway-grid">
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4><code>log</code></h4>
					<p>Just log the response. Good for testing — check the gateway logs to see what the agent would do.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4><code>github_comment</code></h4>
					<p>Post the response back as a comment on the issue or PR that triggered it.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="gateway-card">
					<h4><code>discord</code> / <code>slack</code> / <code>telegram</code></h4>
					<p>Forward the response to your configured messaging channel.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p>Filter by event type using <code>events</code> — only listed types trigger the agent. The agent handles finer-grained logic (like ignoring edits or bot authors) via the prompt.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="step-block">
			<h3><span class="step-label">Step 9</span> Run it</h3>
			<pre><code>./lastlight</code></pre>
			<p>That's it. You can also run single commands:</p>
			<pre><code>./lastlight chat -q "Review the latest PR on yourname/your-repo"
./lastlight chat -q "Triage open issues on yourname/another-repo"</code></pre>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Built-in skills -->
	<section class="skills">
		<h2>Tricks up its sleeve</h2>
		<div class="skills-grid">
			<div class="skill">
				<code>/pr-review</code>
				<p>Review a PR with structured, severity-ranked feedback</p>
			</div>
			<div class="skill">
				<code>/issue-triage</code>
				<p>Label, deduplicate, and prioritize issues</p>
			</div>
			<div class="skill">
				<code>/repo-health</code>
				<p>Generate a health report with metrics and action items</p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://github.com/users/cliftonc/projects/4" class="skill skill-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
				<strong>Want more?</strong>
				<p>Check the roadmap for what's coming next</p>
			</a>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Schedule -->
	<section class="schedule">
		<h2>Pick your mode</h2>
		<p class="section-desc">Webhooks and cron handle the same jobs — use one or the other, not both.</p>

		<div class="gateway-grid">
			<div class="gateway-card">
				<h4>Webhooks <span class="badge-warn" style="color: var(--teal); background: rgba(26, 122, 138, 0.12);">recommended</span></h4>
				<p>Real-time. GitHub sends events as they happen — issues triaged instantly, PRs reviewed on open. Requires a public endpoint.</p>
				<div class="schedule-table" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
					<div class="schedule-row header">
						<span>Event</span>
						<span>Response</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>Issue opened</span>
						<span class="freq">Instant</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>PR opened</span>
						<span class="freq">Instant</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>@mention from maintainer</span>
						<span class="freq">Builds a feature</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="gateway-card">
				<h4>Cron</h4>
				<p>Periodic sweeps. No public endpoint needed — the agent polls GitHub on a schedule. Simpler to set up, but slower to respond.</p>
				<div class="schedule-table" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
					<div class="schedule-row header">
						<span>Job</span>
						<span>Frequency</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>Triage new issues</span>
						<span class="freq">Every 15 min</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>Check PRs awaiting review</span>
						<span class="freq">Every 30 min</span>
					</div>
					<div class="schedule-row">
						<span>Weekly health report</span>
						<span class="freq">Mondays 9am</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="section-note">The weekly health report runs regardless of mode — it's useful either way.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Footer -->
	<footer>
		<div class="footer-content">
			<img src="/logo.png" alt="Last Light" width="32" height="32" />
			<p>MIT License. Built with <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hermes Agent</a>. <a href="https://github.com/users/cliftonc/projects/4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Roadmap</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</footer>

</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
	:root {
		--gold: #F0B429;
		--orange: #E8752A;
		--teal: #1A7A8A;
		--teal-dark: #135E6B;
		--navy: #1B2735;
		--bg: #0C1117;
		--bg-card: #141B24;
		--bg-card-hover: #1A2332;
		--border: #1E2A38;
		--text: #C9D1D9;
		--text-muted: #7D8694;
		--text-bright: #ECEFF4;
		--mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
		--sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
	}

	* {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	html {
		scroll-behavior: smooth;
	}

	body {
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--text);
		font-family: var(--sans);
		line-height: 1.6;
		-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
	}

	a {
		color: var(--gold);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	a:hover {
		color: var(--orange);
	}

	h1, h2, h3 {
		color: var(--text-bright);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	code {
		font-family: var(--mono);
